<TITLE> Explosion hits military vehicle in Turkish city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DIYARBAKIR, Turkey, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - An explosion struck a military vehicle in the centre of the southeast Turkish city of Diyarbakir on Thursday, injuring many people, witnesses said. Turkey's state Anatolian news agency said the explosion was caused by a bomb. Diyarbakir is the biggest city of mainly Kurdish southeast Turkey and home to large numbers of troops who are battling PKK Kurdish rebels both inside Turkey and in nearby northern Iraq.
